2026-04-12: PostgreSQL with JSONB flexible metadata storage
  - Strong ACID guarantees chosen over NoSQL; prevents subtle distributed consistency bugs
  - JSONB columns (settings, metadata) provide flexibility without sacrificing schema strictness
  - Composite indexes (project_id, status, due_date) + GIN on JSONB + partial indexes on active records
  - Flyway migrations version-controlled; blue-green deployment enables zero-downtime schema changes
  - PgBouncer connection pooling mandatory; VACUUM jobs prevent table bloat from UPDATE-heavy workloads
  - Scales to <10M records efficiently; sharding deferred until 100M+
